#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.42"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.42:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.42:0.2"
msgid "5. Rohitassavagga "
msgstr "5. With Rohitassa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.42:0.3"
msgid "42. Pañhabyākaraṇasutta "
msgstr "42. Ways of Answering Questions "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: pañhabyākaraṇāni → pañhābyākaraṇāni (mr)
msgctxt "an4.42:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, pañhabyākaraṇāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four ways of answering questions. "

msgctxt "an4.42:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.42:1.3"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, pañho ekaṃsabyākaraṇīyo; "
msgstr "There is a question that should be answered definitively. "

msgctxt "an4.42:1.4"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, pañho vibhajjabyākaraṇīyo; "
msgstr "There is a question that should be answered analytically. "

msgctxt "an4.42:1.5"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, pañho paṭipucchābyākaraṇīyo; "
msgstr "There is a question that should be answered with a counter-question. "

msgctxt "an4.42:1.6"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, pañho ṭhapanīyo. "
msgstr "There is a question that should be set aside. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.42:1.7"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri pañhabyākaraṇānīti. "
msgstr "These are the four ways of answering questions. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.42:2.1"
msgid "Ekaṃsavacanaṃ ekaṃ, "
msgstr "One is stated definitively, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:2.2"
msgid "vibhajjavacanāparaṃ; "
msgstr "another analytically, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:2.3"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ paṭipuccheyya, "
msgstr "a third with a counter-question, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:2.4"
msgid "catutthaṃ pana ṭhāpaye. "
msgstr "while a fourth is set aside. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: tesaṃ → nesaṃ (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.42:3.1"
msgid "Yo ca tesaṃ tattha tattha, "
msgstr "A mendicant who knows each of these, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:3.2"
msgid "jānāti anudhammataṃ; "
msgstr "in line with good principles, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:3.3"
msgid "Catupañhassa kusalo, "
msgstr "is said to be skilled "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:3.4"
msgid "āhu bhikkhuṃ tathāvidhaṃ. "
msgstr "in the four kinds of questions. "

# NOTE: Comm: Durāsado duppasahoti parehi ghaṭṭetuṃ vā abhibhavituṃ vā na sakkā
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.42:4.1"
msgid "Durāsado duppasaho, "
msgstr "They’re intimidating, hard to defeat, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:4.2"
msgid "gambhīro duppadhaṃsiyo; "
msgstr "deep, and hard to crush. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:4.3"
msgid "Atho atthe anatthe ca, "
msgstr "They’re expert in both "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ubhayassa hoti kovido → ubhayatthassa kovido (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.42:4.4"
msgid "ubhayassa hoti kovido. "
msgstr "what the meaning is and what it isn’t. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.42:5.1"
msgid "Anatthaṃ parivajjeti, "
msgstr "Rejecting what is not the meaning, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:5.2"
msgid "atthaṃ gaṇhāti paṇḍito; "
msgstr "an astute person grasps the meaning. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:5.3"
msgid "Atthābhisamayā dhīro, "
msgstr "A wise one, comprehending the meaning, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.42:5.4"
msgid "paṇḍitoti pavuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "is called ‘astute’.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.42:5.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
